### 3. Repository Layer (`orderDetail.repository.ts`)

**Key Responsibility:** Data transformation from DTO to domain model

**Transformation Logic:**

```typescript
function getTransactionFromOrderDetail(dto: OrderDetailDataDto): PointsTransaction {
  // 1. Calculate total value from items
  const totalValue = items.reduce((sum, item) => 
    sum + (item.unitaryValue * item.quantity), 0);

  // 2. Build detail fields array combining items + benefits
  const fields = [];
  items.forEach(item => fields.push({
    label: `Item ${index + 1}`,
    value: `${item.description} - ${quantity}x R$ ${unitaryValue.toFixed(2)}`,
  }));

  benefits.forEach(benefit => fields.push({
    label: `Benefício ${index + 1}`,
    value: `${benefit.description} - R$ ${Math.abs(benefit.value).toFixed(2)}`,
  }));

  // 3. Map to PointsTransaction format
  return {
    id: dto.id,
    date: dto.date,
    description: dto.description,
    type: 'RESCUE',                    // Hard-coded to RESCUE type
    amount: dto.amount,
    currencyValue: totalValue > 0 ? totalValue : Math.abs(dto.amount),
    icon: 'icon-cashback',
    details: {
      provider: 'Cashback',
      extraInfo: '',
      fields,
    },
    status: '',
    marketplace: dto.marketplace,      // Marketplace data passed through
  };
}
```

**Response Validation:**
- Checks `returnCode` (200 or 0 indicates success)
- Returns `null` for invalid responses

